In Pycharm
ðŸ“Œ Step 1: Go to Project Interpreter Settings

    At the top, click File > Settings (or PyCharm > Preferences on Mac).

    In the left sidebar, go to Project: your_project_name > Python Interpreter.

ðŸ“Œ Step 2: Add Libraries

    On the Python Interpreter page, click the "+" button (usually at the top right of the package list).

ðŸ“Œ Step 3: Install OpenCV

    In the search bar, type opencv-python.

    Select opencv-python from the list.

    Click Install Package (at the bottom).

ðŸ“Œ Step 4: Install Mediapipe

    In the same search bar, type mediapipe.

    Select mediapipe from the list.

    Click Install Package.

DISCLAIMER: Mediapipe won't run in the latest Python version. In order to run Mediapipe, you must either set up a virtual environment or download a lower version of Python, ideally 3.10.1
